# ENDOS FAQ

## What is ENDOS?

ENDOS stands for Enterprise Navigation & Decision Operating System. It is a platform concept for better executive navigation under uncertainty.

## Is ENDOS a dashboard?

No. Dashboards are one possible interface. ENDOS is intended as a broader decision and navigation system that can include dashboards, knowledge objects, methods, validation logic and executive workflows.

## What is the current maturity level?

Foundation stage. The repository, GitHub Pages site and documentation baseline are established. Functional modules will be added sprint by sprint.

## What is the next implementation step?

Sprint 2: Executive Mission Control.

## What makes ENDOS different?

ENDOS focuses on adaptive relevance, executive attention, uncertainty, evidence, method orchestration and enterprise navigation rather than static reporting alone.

## Who is ENDOS for?

Potential users include executives, controllers, enterprise architects, consultants, strategy teams, transformation leaders, risk managers and pilot customers in complex organizations.
